ng the command" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 12 "with(plots
);" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 103 "Notice all the various commands c
ontained in this package.  Many of them should \"ring a bell\" with yo
u." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 82 "The
 command for graphing implicit relations (the conic sections for examp
le) is   " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 256 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 64 "implicitplot(relation in x and y, x=a..b,y=c..d, optional stuff
)" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 65 "9.  \+
On the same axes plot the graphs of the following conics     " }
{XPPEDIT 18 0 "x^2+i*y^2 = 1;" "6#/,&*$%\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"*&%\"iGF(*$%\"y
GF'F(F(F(" }{TEXT -1 69 "   for i = -3, -2, -1, 0, 1, 2, 3. View the g
raph in 1-1 perspective." }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "
" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 67 "10.   On the same axes plot the grap
hs of the following circles    " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(x+k)^2+y^2 = 1;" "6#
